    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": false,
    "title": "wallet: Replace assert(false) with CHECK_NONFATAL(false) in EncryptWallet",
    "user": {
      "login": "TianYuBaBg",
      "id": 30548182,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwNTQ4MTgy",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/30548182?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/TianYuBaBg",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/TianYuBaBg/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "The two `assert(false)` calls in `CWallet::EncryptWallet()` handle unrecoverable states: an SPKM `Encrypt()` failing partway through the loop, and `TxnCommit()` failing. In both cases the in-memory wallet state is inconsistent.\n\n`CHECK_NONFATAL(false)` is the existing pattern for fatal logic errors in RPC code paths, used in `wallet/rpc/backup.cpp`, `wallet/rpc/coins.cpp`, and elsewhere. It throws `NonFatalCheckError` which the RPC server catches and returns as `RPC_MISC_ERROR`. In debug/fuzz builds with `ABORT_ON_FAILED_ASSUME` it also calls `assertion_fail()`, preserving the original crash behavior.\n\nThe `mapMasterKeys` entry inserted before the loop is also erased on failure, so `HasEncryptionKeys()` does not incorrectly report the wallet as encrypted afterward.",
